3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The Hamiltonian cycle problem is a classic problem in algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the NP-completeness of the Hamiltonian cycle problem for supergrid graphs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper's application of the Hamiltonian cycle problem to control the stitching trace of computerized sewing machines could potentially fall under the domain of game theory.
